Program: Start the Week
Title: 24/05/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00sfw4b
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 24 May 2010
On Start the Week on Monday the psychologist Dorothy Rowe asks why we lie. Andrew Marr confronts death with the neuroscientist David Eagleman, who has written a series of stories about the afterlife. Ian Buruma reflects on democracy and religion around the world, and viewing it all from the sidelines is Simon Baker, co-curator of an exhibition about voyeurism and photography. Producer: Katy Hickman. Show less